	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Puzzles Solved? Castersrealm Article Thinks So!</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=572123" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abm.asp?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
The puzzle pieces have kept us all busy, but Baelish seems to have found a solution! Yesterday, in his <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4245" target="_blank">article on Caster's Realm</a>, Baelish gives details from a PC Gamer Magazine article on Star Wars Galaxies, in which, minor details regarding the creation of the EverQuest 2 project are revealed. 
<p>
Could the puzzle pieces be linking to this supposed EverQuest 2 project? If so, we're in for some good Fippy Snax (TM), because according to Baelish's article, the game will sport the new engine created for Star Wars Galaxies, experience debts (instead of losing experience, you gain a debt), new zones, redone zones, 3 continents, and more. 
<p>
<b><i><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=4245" target="_blank">Go read Baelish's article on Caster's Realm Now!</a></b></i></blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=572123">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
		</tr>

		</table>

	</td>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
</tr>
